HEADWORD: Repoussage
<hw>Re*pous`sage"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Repouss⟦eacute⟧</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Art)</fld> <def>Art or process of
hammering out or pressing thin metal from the reverse side: (1) in
producing repouss⟦eacute⟧ work; (2) in leveling up any part of an etched
plate that has been worked so as to cause a depression.</def>⟦br⟧
